<item>
            <title>[LU-11029] passing a valid pointer to PTR_ERR</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11029</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Passing of valid pointers to PTR_ERR is unlikely to lead to desired effects, so we really need to do something about it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;one example:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;        wobdo = object_update_param_get(update, 0, &amp;amp;size);
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (IS_ERR(wobdo) || size != sizeof(*wobdo)) {
                CERROR(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;%s: obdo is NULL, invalid RPC: rc = %ld\n&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,
                       tgt_name(tsi-&amp;gt;tsi_tgt), PTR_ERR(wobdo));
                RETURN(PTR_ERR(wobdo));
        }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;List of triggers:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;lustre/target/out_handler.c:120 out_create() warn: passing a valid pointer to &apos;PTR_ERR&apos;
